TopicTitle: LLL - Lack Luster Labs - Development Thread

Articles.Content:
Nice to see that some work has been started already. This is my favorite parts pack. Did you guys already know about the solar panels deploying funky? If you do so in the VAB they are 90 degrees off, and if done so on mission they spontaneously self-destruct on deploying.

EDIT Also have found the two side by side nodes on the farings are backwards.

Edited May 24, 2015 by DigitalProeliator

Nice to see that some work has been started already. This is my favorite parts pack. Did you guys already know about the solar panels deploying funky? If you do so in the VAB they are 90 degrees off, and if done so on mission they spontaneously self-destruct on deploying.

EDIT Also have found the two side by side nodes on the farings are backwards.

Thanks, we'll try to track this down, but I'm not sure what we can do for certain things not working with only config file editing.

Not a problem. Im in the same boat as you guys lol. I'm post any new bugs as I find them so everyone can be on the lookout for them. Sinking a multi launch Duna ISRU mission because of some bad Solar panels is not fun. But speaking of ISRU what do you guys think of adding Ore to the modular tanks?

Edit: After a little more messing around I found the panels DO deploy correctly just the radial attachment node for them is backwards. I guess the shaking from one or more deploying incorrectly caused the others to shake apart.

I am currently fixing up Katallian's fixes with some of the ones I've talked about. Current progress is:

probes now have appropriate SAS modules, while command pods now don't have those (you must rely on pilots).

all engines have been balanced against their counterparts.

The Nerva's are now LF only, which is a 0.5 increase to LF usage compared to previous, but with an LF only tank, should allow you to go farther.

Heat shield/ debris shield now has ablater.

fixed the shrouded solar panel

The Omni radar now has Orbital Scanner modules.

Rotating dishes now have narrow band scanner functionality.

radar now has ground scanner functionality.

I am currently setting all parts to have appropriate max temp 2400 versus old 3400. Still have to finish over 2/3 of the remaining parts, and fix the bi-couplers attachment points.

Okay, I have finished my changes to LLL, there still may be some problems. Hope this holds people over till Lack can do a proper fix.

https://www.dropbox.com/home/LLL%20Fixed%201.0.2

Change Log (Dakota2063)

*rebalanced engines against stock counterparts

*Command pods had SAS removed for manned vessels

*Probes now have levelled SAS module so that they can perform like probe counterparts

*Debris/Heat shields now have 2400 ablator, and max temp reduced to 3400 as per stock heat shields.

*Omni radar now has orbital scanner functionality

*Radar now has surface scanner functionality

*Both rotating dishes now has Narrow band scanner functionality

*Fixed orientation of shrouded solar panel

*Added Stock ISRU functionality to Kethane converter and changed it's name.

*Fixed Bi-coupler bottom nodes.

*Reduced max Temperature by roughly 1000 to be more inline with current max heat values.

*Removed min and max scale from scale file as it now causes problems with new Tweakscale mod.

Change Log (Katalliaan)

*Changed cargo containers over to KIS

*Changed R&D tech that no longer existed

*Fixed nodes, so that parts connect properly.

Known issues

*Cargo drop bay legs have issue with being placed. can be first part, but does not like being placed otherwise. (Don't know how to fix)

*Air intakes don't have proper drag cubes, as with most other parts, and will drag more then other air intakes.

*Habitation ring not fixed, space in between arms.

Just as a question do any of you have any issues with the LLL Tug? It will grip onto something when I bump into it and I can let it go, but the item seams to no longer be effected by gravity... Oh and for the 2x1 landing legs Ive noticed they DO work, just spawn on the bottom of the VAB or SPH. You can then pick it up and use it as normal. Why it does this I have no idea.

Here's a quick patch for something we missed and some added functionality with Extraplanetary Launchpads:

  • The 2x1 ISRU no longer has Kethane as a dependency in .
  • The 2(2x1) Workshop is now properly an Extraplanetary Launchpads workshop with the ability to convert Metal into RocketParts, and now requires Extraplanetary Launchpads instead of TAC Life Support.
  • Added a ModuleManager file that allows the ISRU to handle MetalOre to Metal and ScrapMetal to Metal for use in Extraplanetary Launchpads. It's a tweak I had made for myself for the stock ISRU, but I understand if you don't want to use it.

Link

Note that this is just a differential patch; you still need Dakota's link.

Why all the new pointless dependancies. LLL never needed them before. My machine has enough of a challenge loading mods this size without forcing another un-NEEDED mod to be added. I used those parts just fine without Connected.

If you want to make them recommended, fine. Needed? Why? Why the hell does berty need Connected???????

And why do I suddenly NEED deadly reentry? Isn't the new atmosphere challenging enough?

A patch that says "NEEDS[DeadlyReentry]" doesn't mean that the part won't work without DR. It means that the patch will not execute (and modify the part config) unless DR is installed. Same for Connected Living Space. Those patches add CLS and DR modules to parts if and only if you have the mods in question (otherwise, KSP will whine about not being able to find a "ModuleConnectedLivingSpace" or what have you).

Ummm not so. At least not in my case. I downloaded Dakota's fix... and mind you, thanks for helping Lack get this patched... and I might have had a dozen LLL parts, until I begrudgingly installed yet another mod, CLS.

Module manager may be a nice toy but here's my opinion. If a part doesn't absolutely NEED another mod, don't tell module manager. Module manager is stupid to the point that it simply disables things and doesn't tell the end user what or why.

If new users, those who could care less about getting down to the file level download LLL and like I did, find less than a dozen parts, the'll remove it. And ya know what, LLL is one of the best mods out there. That... would suck.

Fengist: The ModuleManager files in Dakota's package are identical to those in Lack's 0.90 download. You can run their contents through any diff tool to confirm that. I just checked in my install (with the only mods LLL has support for being KIS and Extraplanetary Launchpads) and I have something like 150 parts, not "a dozen".

Additionally, ModuleManager does exactly as it's told - if it can't figure out what you were trying to do, it'll throw an error and move on to the next node (or file if it's the entire file). It doesn't outright remove parts.

Yea I also have dozens of parts and im playing through a career mode game with only half the tech tree unlocked.... If you absolutly insist on not having the MM files you can delete them but as Kerbas said if you don't have the mod stated in the MM file it will be skipped.
